Usage: msys2-mirror.sh [OPTION]... [--] [MIRROR_PATH]...

Download latest MSYS2 setup, database and files from a remote mirror.
This can be used to clone a remote MSYS2 repository, for instance to
install MSYS2 on offline computers.

Use pv if available for progress reporting.

Options:
  -h, --help    Print this help

  --mingw32     Download mingw32 db and files
  --mingw32-db  Download mingw32 db only (default)
  --no-mingw32  Do not download mingw32 db or files

  --mingw64     Download mingw64 db and files
  --mingw64-db  Download mingw64 db only (default)
  --no-mingw64  Do not download mingw64 db or files

  --msys        Download msys db and files (default)
  --msys-db     Download msys db only
  --no-msys     Do not download msys db or files

Examples:
    # Create a new local mirror (with mingw32/64 db only)
    git clone https://github.com/xeyownt/msys2-mirror.git
    cd msys2-mirror
    ./msys2-mirror.sh

    # Update an existing local mirror
    cd msys2-mirror
    git pull
    ./msys2-mirror.sh

    # Update an existing local mirror with mingw32/64
    cd msys2-mirror
    git pull
    ./msys2-mirror.sh --mingw32 --mingw64
